column5: It goes like this  Jig Jig Jig........... PiG  big PiG  net.........      Bonus Walleye    FOr a little while now and again in fall there's no place I'd rather be for HUGE smallies.
Some fatties, I have never fished for smallies in may, what is the presentation?
Nice phatties. Love the santa hat lol don't stand infront of the GPS next time
great fish. some serious fatties there !! thanks for sharing
Great fish, Denis. Love the Santa hat....not that I was looking there.
I had to look back to see the santa hat, I was looking too high LOL  Great smallies Denis, and congrats on the 1st place finish in the Millenium Tourney!
Great fish bud!  I am planning a trip hopefully for next week!
beauty fish ! getting out on Erie is defenetly on my "to-do list" just need to find some one to go with

nice fish Dennis.  guessing those are the fish from last saturday with that tell tale black spot  great win on Sat. this weekend looking a little too rough for my liking. would love to have been out there today though.  ryan
The wind tomorrow looks ok but saturday is calling for west 30mph with gusts up 50mph, I guess it's a coin flip for saturday.
alright there Denis nice fat smallies there chunky little buggers arent they cant wait for bass opener now
Holy smokes those fish are fat!  "Huge smallies" is an oxymoron.LOL  Nicely done Denis
this is too nuts...I must fish these

They just updated forecast and it's gonna be sustained winds @ 30 gusting over 50mph.  In other words don't bother this weekend, next weekend is the make a wish.  First prize is 4000k I think and you get a chicken dinner.
What is it 70 bucks CND to get a licence for NY.  I'm thinking about getting one and getting in on the action.  Very nice fish there.  Did you get a weight on any of them?
I believe it's 60 bucks for the licence.  11.97 for those 2 fish
